When I say DSL I mean external DSL, not a fluent interface.<p>So an example of the problem I deal with is a database migration. Let&#x27;s say we have an entity with a value<p>entity SqlTable {
  List<TableColumn> nestedTuple;
}<p>value TableColumn {
  int i;
}<p>and if I change column type in value object to long I want my compilers to prepare a DB migration with the appropriate SQL statements for the specific DB I use. Of course, there is nothing too complex about it, but it&#x27;s not trivial either (in this case you have to prepare a second field, unnest the whole hierarchy to get to the nested field, copy it to new type and compact the hierarchy back again).<p>I find it costly since there are gazillion of such features. And when they start interacting with each other things gets messy.
